## Step 2: Calculate Initial APP Mass

Let me calculate the current mass of the `quote` function.

```
export const quote = (items: Array<{ type: string; cursed?: boolean }>, customer: unknown, contractNumber: number): number => {
  const componentCounts: Record<string, number> = {};
  for (const item of items) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.includes(item.type)) {
      componentCounts[item.type] = (componentCounts[item.type] ?? 0) + 1;
    }
  }

  let totalPremium = 0;

  for (const item of items) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.includes(item.type) && componentCounts[item.type] === BLOCK_SIZE) {
      continue;
    }
    const basePremium = BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] ?? 0;
    totalPremium += applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge(basePremium);
    if (item.cursed) {
      totalPremium += basePremium * CURSED_SURCHARGE_RATE;
    }
  }

  for (const type of COMPONENT_TYPES) {
    if (componentCounts[type] === BLOCK_SIZE) {
      totalPremium += applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge(BLOCK_PREMIUM);
    }
  }

  return Math.ceil(totalPremium) + PROCESSING_FEE;
};
```

**Component Count (quote function body only)**:
- Constants: `{}`, `0`, `1`, `0`, `0` = 5 (mass: 5)
- Bindings: `items`, `customer`, `contractNumber`, `componentCounts`, `item` (loop 1), `item` (loop 2), `totalPremium` (initial), `basePremium`, `type` (loop 3) = 9 (mass: 9)
- Invocations: `COMPONENT_TYPES.includes` (x3), `componentCounts[item.type]` (x3 lookups), `BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type]`, `applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge` (x2), `Math.ceil`, `+` operators... let me be more precise and count actual function calls:
